\section{The hash chain}{


Every entry stores the SHA-256 hash of all prior entries:

\if{html}{\out{<div class="sourceCode">}}\preformatted{h_0 = SHA256("GENESIS" | app | version | timestamp)
h_n = SHA256(entry_id | timestamp | app | version | user | type |
             <payload fields> | h_\{n-1\})
}\if{html}{\out{</div>}}

Altering any field in any entry — including the timestamp or reason — breaks
the chain from that entry forward. \code{\link[=verify_log]{verify_log()}} recomputes every hash and
reports the first broken link. This works offline, from the raw \code{.rlog}
file, without an active R session.
}

